com.opengamma.strata.basics.market

Interface MarketDataId<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the market data identified by the identifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CurveId, IndexCurveId, ObservableId, RateCurveId
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CurveGroupId, CurveInputsId, DiscountCurveId, FxRateId, IborIndexCurveId, IndexRateId, IsdaIndexCreditCurveInputsId, IsdaIndexRecoveryRateId, IsdaSingleNameCreditCurveInputsId, IsdaSingleNameRecoveryRateId, IsdaYieldCurveInputsId, MissingMappingId, NoMatchingRuleId, OvernightIndexCurveId, PriceIndexCurveId, QuoteId, SwaptionVolatilitiesId

    public interface MarketDataId<T>
    An identifier for a unique item of market data.

    The market data system can locate market data using implementations of this interface. Implementations can identify any piece of market data. This includes observable values, such as the quoted market value of a security, and derived values, such as a volatility surface or a discounting curve.

    Note that this interface is typically used by the market data system and not by applications. Application code will generally use MarketDataKey, with a mapping step to convert the key to a MarketDataId.

    See Also:
